Let s \colon  B \to  A and r \colon  A \to  B be a pair of maps. A homotopy h \colon  r\circ  s \sim  1_{B} exhibits s as a section of r and r as a retraction of s. Together, 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen s,r\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 are referred to as a section-retraction pair.
